  "text": "The C-Jun 3′-UTR was cloned into the pGL3-CM as previously described between the Bgl II and Mlu I sites [CITATION_1] . Overlapping PCR was performed to mutate the miR-139 target site in the Smad4 3′-UTR, using two additional primers, and the products were subcloned into pGL3-CM. R (WT)-luc was constructed by cloning the distal region upstream of miR-139 into pGL3-promoter reporter construct, and R(ΔJunBS)-luc was obtained by mutating Jun binding site through overlapping PCR.",
